<item>
  <title>An Introduction to Magic Squares</title>
  <dc:creator>Hyun Joon</dc:creator>
  <link>https://your-website-url.example.com/posts/intro/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<section id="magic-squares" class="level1">
<h1>1.Magic Squares</h1>
<p>A magic square is a square grid of usually positive natural numbers whose sums of the numbers in each row, column, and diagonals are the same.<br>
Here are a few examples,</p>
<div class="quarto-figure quarto-figure-center">
<figure class="figure">
<p><img src="https://your-website-url.example.com/posts/intro/magic_square1.png" class="img-fluid figure-img"></p>
<figcaption>the famous one</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cbegin%7Barray%7D%7Bc%7Cc%7Cc%7D%0A17%20&amp;%20113%20&amp;%2047%20%5C%5C%20%5Chline%0A89%20&amp;%2059%20&amp;%2029%20%5C%5C%20%5Chline%0A71%20&amp;%205%20&amp;%20101%0A%5Cend%7Barray%7D%0A"><br>
This one is made of primes. It’s sum is 177</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cbegin%7Barray%7D%7Bc%7Cc%7Cc%7Cc%7D%0A7%20&amp;%2012%20&amp;%201%20&amp;%2014%20%5C%5C%20%5Chline%0A2%20&amp;%2013%20&amp;%208%20&amp;%2011%20%5C%5C%20%5Chline%0A16%20&amp;%203%20&amp;%2010%20&amp;%205%20%5C%5C%20%5Chline%0A9%20&amp;%206%20&amp;%2015%20&amp;%204%0A%5Cend%7Barray%7D%0A"><br>
This one is 4 by 4 and sums to 34</p>
</section>
<section id="magic-square-of-squares" class="level1">
<h1>2.Magic square of squares</h1>
<p>A magic square is a magic square of square if the numbers in each cell can be squared and the resulting grid is also a magic square.<br>
No 3 by 3 magic square of squares has been found, but other magic square of squares have been.</p>
<p>Here’s one found by Euler. Its sum is 8,515. <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cbegin%7Barray%7D%7Bc%7Cc%7Cc%7Cc%7D%0A68%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%2029%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%2041%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%2037%5E%7B2%7D%20%5C%5C%20%5Chline%0A17%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%2031%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%2079%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%2032%5E%7B2%7D%20%5C%5C%20%5Chline%0A59%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%2028%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%2023%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%2061%5E%7B2%7D%20%5C%5C%20%5Chline%0A11%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%2077%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%208%5E%7B2%7D%20&amp;%2049%5E%7B2%7D%0A%5Cend%7Barray%7D%0A"></p>


</section>

 ]]></description>
